<item>
            <title>[SPR-1600] The XML bean definitions parser fails when using schema namepsace prefix for the beans namespace</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-1600</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m taking a first look at Spring 2.0, this is done by upgrading a Spring 1.2.6 based application. I transformed all of my&lt;br/&gt;
DTD based configuration files to schema based configuration files using the following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;sp:beans  xmlns:sp=&quot;http://www.springframework.org/schema/beans&quot;   &amp;lt;--With a namespace prefix&lt;br/&gt;
xmlns:xsi=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem is that Spring fails to find any bean, when omitting  the namespace prefix, as in&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;beans  xmlns=&quot;http://www.springframework.org/schema/beans&quot; &amp;lt;-- w/o a namespace prefix&lt;br/&gt;
xmlns:xsi=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It works.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My suggestion &lt;br/&gt;
I looked on the code a little bit and from a quick look I can see on DefaultXmlBeanDefinitionParser.jave:&lt;br/&gt;
........&lt;br/&gt;
line 380: else if (BEAN_ELEMENT.equals(ele.getNodeName())) {&lt;br/&gt;
........&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I suspect that ele.getLocalName() would solve the problem (on line 380 and some other places on the file)&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
